==English==
===Suffix===
'''-rix''', plural '''[[-rices]]'''

# Suffix appended to words, usually agent nouns ending in '''[[-or]]''', to create a female form.

====Examples====

{|
!  Male || Female
|-
| aviator || aviatrix
|-
| executor&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; || executrix 
|}

====Etymology====
From Latin '''-rix'''

====Usage note====
The form ending in '''-rix''' is the original Latin form, but this has in many cases developed into the form ending in '''-ess''' instead, as with "actor, actress" (as opposed to the earlier "actor, actrix").

===Related Terms===
*[[-ess]]
*[[-or]]

