*[[-ette]]
*[[she-]]

==Latin==
===Suffix===
'''-rix''', ''f'', plural '''-rices'''

[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|Third declension]]

# Suffix used to form feminine versions of agent nouns ending in '''[[-or]]''', often appended to the root of a perfect passive participle. Always preceded by the letter ''t'' (''-trix''), a common perfect passive participle ending.
# Suffix used to form feminine versions of adjectives (in the same way as above), often with a poetic quality and/or a negative connotation.

====Examples====
{|
!  Male || Female
|-
| actor || actrix
|-
| dominator&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; || dominatrix
|-
| victor || victrix
|}

===Related Terms===
*[[-or]]

